1 break out the code into mutiple files. 

Sure, let's break down the functions from your sketch into separate files:

Main Sketch File (main.ino):
Contains setup and loop functions.
Includes global variables and the main control flow.
GPSModule.h/.cpp:
Functions related to GPS data processing and handling.
getGPS()
publishGPSData()
LCDModule.h/.cpp:
Functions related to LCD display management.
displayTimeAndDate()
displayWaitingForGPS()
rotateInfoDisplay()
TimeModule.h/.cpp:
Functions related to time management and adjustments.
adjustTimeZone()
calculateTimeZoneOffset()
SerialModule.h/.cpp:
Functions related to serial communication and debugging.
debugPrint()
sendDataViaSerial()
UtilityFunctions.h/.cpp:
Utility functions used across modules.
hdopDescription()
printTime()
Here's how you would organize these functions into separate files:

main.ino:
Contains setup, loop, and global variables.
Includes: main.ino
GPSModule.h/.cpp:
Header file (GPSModule.h): Contains function declarations and any necessary includes.
Functions: getGPS(), publishGPSData()
Source file (GPSModule.cpp): Implements the functions declared in GPSModule.h.
Includes: GPSModule.h, Arduino.h, TimeLib.h, TinyGPS++.h
LCDModule.h/.cpp:
Header file (LCDModule.h): Contains function declarations and any necessary includes.
Functions: displayTimeAndDate(), displayWaitingForGPS(), rotateInfoDisplay()
Source file (LCDModule.cpp): Implements the functions declared in LCDModule.h.
Includes: LCDModule.h, Arduino.h, LiquidCrystal_I2C.h, Wire.h
TimeModule.h/.cpp:
Header file (TimeModule.h): Contains function declarations and any necessary includes.
Functions: adjustTimeZone(), calculateTimeZoneOffset()
Source file (TimeModule.cpp): Implements the functions declared in TimeModule.h.
Includes: TimeModule.h, Arduino.h, TimeLib.h
SerialModule.h/.cpp:
Header file (SerialModule.h): Contains function declarations and any necessary includes.
Functions: debugPrint(), sendDataViaSerial()
Source file (SerialModule.cpp): Implements the functions declared in SerialModule.h.
Includes: SerialModule.h, Arduino.h
UtilityFunctions.h/.cpp:
Header file (UtilityFunctions.h): Contains function declarations and any necessary includes.
Functions: hdopDescription(), printTime()
Source file (UtilityFunctions.cpp): Implements the functions declared in UtilityFunctions.h.
Includes: UtilityFunctions.h, Arduino.h 